CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 5, 1946, pg. 13, reads: "Seeing Double! - The New Year looks good to Wendell and William Jackson, twin sons of Mr. and Mrs. Al J. Jackson of 742 Bryn Mawr Road. Their mother can tell them apart, but we'll leave it up to you as to which twin is which.  The gent on the right seems to be enjoying himself bringing in New Year. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Twins Wendell and William Jackson wearing identical outfits and seated in high chairs, in domestic interior with Christmas tree in background, another version
